[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man charged with murdering 84-year-old Brian Robson

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 53-year-old man has been charged with murdering an 84-year-old who was found with serious injuries in a Leicestershire village.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Police found the victim, Brian Robson, injured at a house in Brooklands Road, Cosby, at about 11:30 GMT on Thursday.
He later died in hospital and Peter Bunyan, of Brookfields Road, has been charged with his murder.
Mr Bunyan will appear at Leicester Magistrates' Court on Saturday.
A post-mortem examination has suggested that Mr Robson died as a result of a head injury.
